    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496600>
    dc:description "Fig.2. Examples of nutlets from 11 species of the Schoenus cuspidatus and allies group found in southern Africa:A—S.auritus; B—S.graminifolius; C—S.ligulatus; D—S.exilis; E—S.bolusii; F— S.submarginalis; G—S.crassiculmis; H—S.quartziticus; I—S.limosus; J—S.purpurascens; and K—S.calceolus (immature).The black scale bar represents 1 mm.The mature fruits of S.calceolus and S.prophyllus are unknown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496604>
    dc:description "Fig.4. Examples of plants from six species of the Schoenus cuspidatus andallies group found in southern Africa,showing the corresponding inflorescences and spikelets beneath each plant: A,G and M—S.crassiculmis; B,H and N—S.quartziticus, C,I andO—S.limosus; D,J,and P—S.purpurascens; E,K andQ—S.prophyllus; and F,L and R—S.calceolus. The black scale bar adjacent to the inflorescences in G—L represents 10 mm, while the scale bars adjacent to the spikelets in M—R represent 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496604/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10496630>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Documented locations of Schoenus quartziticus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10496630/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

